liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It's taken him 144 balls and he's had to grind at times, but he's helped settle Australia and proved a vital foil for Travis Head's attacking strokeplay. He gets there with a quick single off his hip to mid on, his most productive zone. A well-paced 50.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 50 for Steve Smith!

children.content: It's taken him 144 balls and he's had to grind at times, but he's helped settle Australia and proved a vital foil for Travis Head's attacking strokeplay.
He gets there with a quick single off his hip to mid on, his most productive zone.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Some 97 runs in that session for Australia for the loss of just one wicket. The sun has come out and the runs have started flowing. Smith has been steady, mixing his brilliant timing with some tentative strokeplay, uncertain about the bounce. Travis Head though, has been excellent, attacking the bad balls and sensibly defending the good ones. It's setting itself up nicely for Australia as things stand heading into the final session of the day.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Tea: Australia 3-170 (Head 60, Smith 33)
